This is apropos of nothing – I guess just that I drank some green tea & did a lead at a recovery meeting and feel really good about life. I'm so grateful to be alive and sober in this incredibly, incredibly weird & screwed up world.

I love sobriety. I love not waking up with hangovers, ever. I love not waking up in weird places. When I find myself in a dangerous situation, I can leave it. If someone calls in the middle of the night, I can wake up and help them. When I'm an asshole, I can cut that shit out.

Rest in peace, Rashad Harden. I feel lucky to have met you.

A favorite memory of DJ Rashad was meeting him outside a club in San Francisco with my co-workers. He had *just* been let in and then kicked out for socking a guy who was aggressively hassling a woman inside the club. Violent, yes, but right-on and hilarious. /3

The DJ gig was like 5 or 6 hours long or something and the text came right in the middle of it. I put on a very long song and left the building to cry. DJ Rashad was legitimately one of the nicest people I've ever met – very easy & real around any type of person. /2

I worked for the booking agency DJ Rashad was with when he passed away. We were close to Rashad – it was a really incredible relationship with him & Spinn and footwork felt monumental. I was DJing a weird corporate gig when the owner texted the news. /1
